# .devcontainer/mount-roots.local.example — TEMPLATE.
# Copy to  .devcontainer/mount-roots.local  and edit with your real paths.
# mount-roots.local is gitignored and MUST NOT be committed (it holds personal host paths).
#
# bin/agent mounts a vault symlink's out-of-vault target into the sandbox ONLY if the target
# sits under one of the roots listed here (fail-closed — anything else is skipped + warned).
# List the host directories your vault symlinks point at, one root per line.
#   - a leading  ~  or  $HOME  is expanded
#   - blank lines and #-comment lines are ignored
#
# Two tiers:
#   <path>          default  — allowlisted on every run
#   optin:<path>    sensitive — allowlisted only when BRAIN_MOUNT_OPTIN=1, so financial/medical
#                   scans and the like stay out of headless and unrelated runs by default.

# Code repos symlinked into projects as dependencies:
$HOME/Code/example-repo

# Coursework / source material referenced read-only by a project:
$HOME/Documents/example-source

# A sensitive root (PII) — mounted only with BRAIN_MOUNT_OPTIN=1:
optin:$HOME/Documents/sensitive-scans
